Dear Editor,

Please consider our manuscript, entitled:
"Under current compiled phenotypic evidence, HIV-1 lenacapavir resistance is driven primarily by mutation identity, whereas subtype adds little explanatory value,"
for publication in Antiviral Research as a Research Article.

This study provides a systematic synthesis of published phenotypic evidence on HIV-1 lenacapavir resistance and a level-of-explanation comparison framework showing that mutation identity explains most currently available resistance variation, while subtype adds little explanatory value at the present data depth. The manuscript also offers a practical surveillance interpretation framework and clear evidence grading to separate robust conclusions from lower-certainty signals.

All analyzed data are from publicly available sources and published reports. No new human or animal experiments were performed, and no additional ethics approval was required. The author declares no competing interests. This work received no external funding.

This manuscript is original, has not been published previously, and is not under consideration elsewhere.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,

Yiheng Yang
School of Future Technology, Dalian University of Technology
